article.title: Outflows of hot molecular gas in ultra-luminous infra-red galaxies mapped with VLT-SINFONI

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the dark contour in Figure 2 represent?
choices: The star formation rate in the NE galaxy.
The distribution of cold molecular gas in the NE galaxy.
The extent of the AGN in the NE galaxy.
An image taken with the Hubble Space Telescope.

multiple_choice_question.text: What is the maximum velocity of the hot molecular H2 gas outflow observed in IRAS 14348-1447?
choices: The maximum velocity cannot be determined from this figure.

multiple_choice_question.text: According to Table 1, what is the estimated total mass outflow rate of molecular gas (hot+cold) in IRAS 12112+0305?
What does Figure 8 show about the presence of a hot H2 counterpart to the CO outflow in IRAS 17208-0014?
choices: It clearly detects the hot H2 counterpart.
It provides a lower limit on the mass of the hot H2 outflow.
It sets an upper limit on the hot-to-cold molecular gas mass ratio.
It confirms that the hot H2 outflow is not present.
